	<transcript sound="sound1"><![CDATA[The process of cleaning and disinfection consists of six basic stages.<br /><br />Pre-cleaning involves removing loose soil by sweeping, wiping or pre-rinsing. A disposable paper towel may be used for this.<br /><br />Main cleaning involves loosening of the surface grease and dirt using hot water and a detergent. A brush or cloth will probably be used.<br /><br />Rinsing with clean, hot water will remove loose dirt and detergent.<br /><br />Disinfection consists of destroying micro-organisms using heat or a chemical disinfectant; sufficient contact time must be allowed for effective disinfection.<br /><br />You may need to rinse again with clean hot water to remove disinfectant. This will depend on the manufacturer's instructions.<br /><br />Drying should preferably be natural, by evaporation. If air-drying is not possible, single-use paper towels or a clean, dry cloth should be used.]]></transcript>

